1
00:00:05,058 --> 00:00:09,628
I wasn't even initiated yet,
I'd joined in May of 1971,

2
00:00:09,631 --> 00:00:11,353
[Disciples as Flower Offerings]

3
00:00:11,353 --> 00:00:14,469
and around June­--July
I was in Los Angeles.

4
00:00:14,469 --> 00:00:17,390
Prabhupād would go for a walk
in the morning.

5
00:00:17,390 --> 00:00:21,108
When he would come back,
around seven o'clock,

6
00:00:21,123 --> 00:00:24,979
we'd all be waiting with flowers.
We'd each have a flower,

7
00:00:24,979 --> 00:00:30,150
and Prabhupād would come
and we'd hand him a flower,

8
00:00:30,150 --> 00:00:35,278
and he'd accept the flower
and then he'd give you a flower.

9
00:00:37,909 --> 00:00:45,876
We didn't know so much about 
protocol or things, but that was nice.

10
00:00:45,876 --> 00:00:51,625
Hand him a flower, he'd accept your
flower, and then give you a flower.

11
00:00:51,625 --> 00:00:55,632
And sometimes, 
Guru Mahārāj, Gurudev,

12
00:00:55,632 --> 00:00:59,823
they considered that really
the disciples,

13
00:00:59,823 --> 00:01:04,005
they shall be considered 
like flowers;

14
00:01:04,036 --> 00:01:08,960
like flower offerings
to the lotus feet of Kṛṣṇa.

15
00:01:09,284 --> 00:01:14,530
Gurudev, I remember, once
on his veranda in Kolkata,

16
00:01:14,576 --> 00:01:20,074
so many devotees were coming,
maybe for the annual festival of some sort,

17
00:01:20,074 --> 00:01:23,075
and his veranda was now filled
with so many,

18
00:01:23,075 --> 00:01:28,287
and he would look out and see in that
small space eighty or a hundred people.

19
00:01:28,287 --> 00:01:34,831
He was overwhelmed, they were
expressing so much appreciation for him,

20
00:01:34,831 --> 00:01:37,759
but he was saying,
on this particular occasion,

21
00:01:37,759 --> 00:01:43,473
"You're all gifts of
Śrila Guru Mahārāj",

22
00:01:43,596 --> 00:01:49,606
and that stuck—
peeked my remembrance.

23
00:01:49,606 --> 00:01:54,313
"Oh, we heard from Srila Prabhupād
so many years ago

24
00:01:54,313 --> 00:02:00,714
that a maha-bhagavata guru
doesn't see anyone as a disciple".

25
00:02:00,714 --> 00:02:03,221
But, and later confirmed by Guru Mahārāj,

26
00:02:03,221 --> 00:02:09,728
rather sees them as vaibhav,
or extensions of his own guru.

